The paper discusses attacks on privacy-preserving algorithms used for sensitive datasets, which are relevant to the fields of computer security (cs.CR) and databases (cs.DB). The attacks involve constructing queries and manipulating noise, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and data science (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the fundamental law of information recovery, which is a concept related to information theory (cs.IT).
